graph LR
    subgraph Compression Algorithms
        direction TB
        NONE[No Compression]
        SNAPPY[Snappy]
        GZIP[Gzip]
        ZSTD[Zstandard]
        LZ4[LZ4]
    end

    subgraph Metrics Comparison
        direction TB

        NONE --> M1[Size: 100%<br/>Read: Fastest<br/>Write: Fastest<br/>CPU: None]

        SNAPPY --> M2[Size: 40-50%<br/>Read: Very Fast<br/>Write: Very Fast<br/>CPU: Low]

        GZIP --> M3[Size: 25-35%<br/>Read: Moderate<br/>Write: Slow<br/>CPU: High]

        ZSTD --> M4[Size: 30-40%<br/>Read: Fast<br/>Write: Fast<br/>CPU: Medium]

        LZ4 --> M5[Size: 45-55%<br/>Read: Very Fast<br/>Write: Very Fast<br/>CPU: Very Low]
    end

    subgraph Use Cases
        direction TB

        M2 --> UC1[Hot Data<br/>Frequent Access<br/>Analytics]

        M3 --> UC2[Cold Storage<br/>Archive<br/>Cost Optimization]

        M4 --> UC3[Balanced<br/>Modern Choice<br/>Good Compression]

        M5 --> UC4[Real-time<br/>Streaming<br/>Low Latency]

        M1 --> UC5[Temporary<br/>Already Compressed<br/>Testing]
    end

    UC1 --> REC[Recommendation]
    UC2 --> REC
    UC3 --> REC

